  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<em>Your form flexes and contorts in unexpected ways, making it difficult for enemies to move you against your will.</em><br/><br/><b>Prerequisites</b><br/>Shapeshifter Style, base attack bonus +5, change shape ability, shapechanger subtype.<br/><br/><b>Benefits</b><br/>While you are using Shapeshifter Style, you gain a +2 bonus to your CMD versus bull rush, drag, grapple, overrun, reposition, and trip combat maneuvers. If you begin your turn with the grappled condition, you can attempt a combat maneuver check or an Escape Artist check as a move action to attempt to break the grapple.<br/><br/><b>Special</b><br/>A character with the wild shape class feature counts as having the change shape ability and shapechanger subtype for the purpose of meeting this feat's prerequisites.",
